Today=E2=80=99s Not Boring is brought to you by=E2=80=A6 WorkOS [ https://s=
ubstack.com/redirect/c845acbb-17c7-458f-a18f-5a75d13b0f28?r=3D9p0gt ]
Building for the enterprise is typically complex, time-consuming, and distr=
acting. Deals sometimes slip away due to strict requirements and technologi=
cal demands from IT admins.=C2=A0
With WorkOS [ https://substack.com/redirect/c845acbb-17c7-458f-a18f-5a75d13=
b0f28?r=3D9p0gt ], startups can sell to large enterprise customers from day=
 one. It=E2=80=99s a set of building blocks for quickly adding features lik=
e Single Sign-On (SAML), Directory Sync (SCIM), and Multi-Factor Authentica=
tion (MFA) with just a few lines of code.
Fast-growing B2B SaaS companies like Loom, PlanetScale, Airbase, and many o=
thers use WorkOS to abstract the integrations between dozens of identity pr=
oviders. Webflow uses WorkOS to serve customers like Zendesk. Vercel levera=
ges WorkOS to land enterprise customers like The Washington Post.
WorkOS [ https://substack.com/redirect/c845acbb-17c7-458f-a18f-5a75d13b0f28=
?r=3D9p0gt ] is an API that increases your TAM. It=E2=80=99s free to get st=
arted and scales with you as you grow.
Hi friends =F0=9F=91=8B,=20
Happy Monday! Big news over here at Not Boring HQ: our daughter, Maya [ htt=
ps://substack.com/redirect/67707a1d-82d6-4698-b026-e3f5ad5c5f8f?r=3D9p0gt ]=
, was born last weekend! =F0=9F=A5=B3 Mom and baby are healthy and happy, a=
nd we=E2=80=99re enjoying the time together as a family.
The plan for my month of paternity leave is to bring in guest writers each =
week who are experts in areas that I think are going to be deeply important=
=2E Last week, we had Kevin Miao join to=20=
talk about securitization on the blo=
ckchain [ https://substack.com/redirect/6a16bce9-80d4-445b-80d6-63480950ff7=
1?r=3D9p0gt ]. Today, we=E2=80=99re bringing in the space cadets from Paylo=
ad Space [ https://substack.com/redirect/01d7992f-c79a-4f45-8e59-0208fb3b66=
a1?r=3D9p0gt ] for an incredibly deep dive on the space economy, in the for=
m of an S-1 for the industry.=20
They nailed it. I was giddy reading the draft that Mo Islam [ https://subst=
ack.com/redirect/ca0c11a4-3dfc-4a9d-b346-3f6c365467d1?r=3D9p0gt ] and Ryan =
Duffy [ https://substack.com/redirect/c1cba6b2-2aa8-446f-84df-ecad9fafea7f?=
r=3D9p0gt ] sent over this week. We=E2=80=99ve touched on space a little bi=
t in Not Boring, and we=E2=80=99ve invested in space companies like Varda [=
 https://substack.com/redirect/077082b7-2cd6-4be3-8b07-3ae6650ef8ac?r=3D9p0=
gt ] and Hadrian [ https://substack.com/redirect/5c27faa0-eac5-44a7-b523-32=
101f860c15?r=3D9p0gt ] (see deep dive [ https://substack.com/redirect/e3eaa=
ece-9e98-4586-9d86-9b8fd1e99490?r=3D9p0gt ]), but I don=E2=80=99t know near=
ly as much as I want to about all of the progress going on in the industry.=
 Space sounds like futuristic sci-fi, and if you=E2=80=99re not familiar, i=
t=E2=80=99s hard to believe how vibrant and multi-faceted the space economy=
 is today.=20
Plus, one of the things I=E2=80=99m most jealous of Dev and Maya about is t=
hat they=E2=80=99re almost certainly going to get to travel to space in the=
ir lifetimes. As a responsible parent, I want to know what they=E2=80=99re =
getting into. =20
There=E2=80=99s no one better at covering space than the Payload team. It=
=E2=80=99s what industry insiders read, and how I=E2=80=99m trying to get u=
p to speed myself, and I=E2=80=99m pumped that they agreed to write a Not B=
oring-style deep dive for us. If you=E2=80=99re at all interested in the =
=E2=80=A6 space =E2=80=A6 and want to stay up-to-date, you need to subscrib=
e to Payload [ https://substack.com/redirect/01d7992f-c79a-4f45-8e59-0208fb=
3b66a1?r=3D9p0gt ].=20
